Commentary Text: Ravi Bishnoi to Krunal Pandya, out Caught by Hooda!! Holed out! The 58-run stand has been broken. Who says leggies can't dismiss left-handed batters? That overthrow did look like one of those moments when KXIP have let it slip earlier in the tournament, but this has more than made up for it. A nothing delivery, to be frank, short and wide, deserved the upper-cut, but with a little more power than it had. Commentary Text: Shami to Suryakumar Yadav, out Caught by Murugan Ashwin!! OH Surya, that's a terrible shot, to end a terrible innings - one in which more than half the balls could have gotten him out! Commentary Text: Boult to Agarwal, no run, huge shout from Boult for caught behind. He's convinced. But de Kock shakes his head immediately and Rohit goes with his keeper's judgement. Boult knew it but couldn't convince anyone else
